Festuca rubra var. rubra

   [6110.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 6110

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A grass spreading by rhizomes. USES The grass is used
   as fodder, hay and pasture particularly for sheep. In ornamental
   horticulture, it is considered one of the best grasses for lawns and is
   also used for erosion control and sports turf. GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. COMMON NAMES Red fescue. FURTHER INF Red fescue may have
   certain winter requirements. Photosynthesis pathway C3. It grows well
   on poor, hilly, sandy or gravelly, dry or wet soil and in shady places.
   Average dry matter yield is about 2.5-3 t/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES (Festuca rubra L. v. rubra)
